     class SBMLLevel1Rule
extends ExplicitRule
    Represent a level 1 rule. This class is used only during the parsing of level 1 files. The real type of a rule will only be determined when we read the attribute 'type'. So on SBMLCoreParser.processEndDocument(org.sbml.jsbml.SBMLDocument) if the level of the model is equal to 1, we loop over the list of rules and clone the rules into RateRule or AssignmentRule.

    As this class is supposed to be used only inside the SBMLCoreParser, it's visibility is put at the package level.

    0.8
